{"index": 286, "title": "Infrastructure Engineer", "job_location": "Cheltenham, England, United Kingdom", "jd_text": "Role Summary:Job Title: Infrastructure Engineer (Mid, Senior, Lead)Job Type: PermanentPay: \u00a340,000 - \u00a375,000 + Bonus + BenefitsBenefits Summary: 25 Days Holiday (+Bank Holidays), Company EV Car Scheme, AXA Healthcare, Company Pension Scheme, Dedicated Training Package/BudgetLocation: Cheltenham (Flexible working available)Security Clearance: None required to start - you will be put through DV ClearanceAbout the client:Our client is an elite technical consultancy that acts as the architectural backbone for some of the UK\u2019s most critical and high-stakes environments. They specialise in engineering bespoke, resilient infrastructure solutions that protect and empower national interests. This isn't just \"IT support\"\u2014this is high-level engineering where you tackle complex, real-world problems that require a blend of sovereign security expertise and cutting-edge innovation. If you want to work at the forefront of digital defence and system resilience within a collaborative, forward-thinking elite squad, this is where you belong.About the job:As an Infrastructure Engineer, you will be a proactive force in the design, implementation, and ongoing evolution of critical IT environments. You will bridge the gap between autonomous problem-solving and collaborative delivery, ensuring that both organisational and customer infrastructures are robust, scalable, and secure. This role is perfect for a technical enthusiast who thrives on variety\u2014one day you might be architecting a virtualised environment, and the next, you could be automating complex system tasks or troubleshooting high-level networking issues.Key Responsibilities:Design and Implementation: Lead the planning and execution of physical and virtual IT infrastructure solutions, ensuring they align perfectly with bespoke customer requirements.Maintenance and Support: Provide high-tier troubleshooting and regular system health monitoring, including patch management, backups, and hardware lifecycles.Documentation: Develop and maintain comprehensive technical documentation for all deployed systems and incident responses to ensure operational excellence.Automation: Create and refine scripts and Infrastructure-as-Code (IaC) tools to drive efficiency and eliminate manual administration tasks.Key Skills:Ansible, Cisco, Juniper, HP, Dell, TCP/IP, DNS, DHCP, VMware, Hyper-V, AWX, Python, PowerShell, BASH, Microsoft, Linux, NetBackup, Veeam, Gitlab, NSD. How to apply:Please either apply through this advert or emailing me directly via jon.mills@searchability.com. For further information please call me: +44 7441 342136. By applying for this role, you give express consent for us to process and submit (subject to required skills) your application to our client in conjunction with this vacancy only.\n\nBegin your response with {\n", "v15_labels": {"loc_raw": "Cheltenham, England, United Kingdom", "loc": "UK_OTHER", "arr_raw": "Flexible working available", "arr": "HYBRID", "sen_raw": "Mid, Senior, Lead", "sen": "LEVEL_3", "tech_raw": "Ansible, Cisco, Juniper, HP, Dell, TCP/IP, DNS, DHCP, VMware, Hyper-V, AWX, Python, PowerShell, BASH, Microsoft, Linux, NetBackup, Veeam, Gitlab, NSD", "tech": ["OOS"], "comp_raw": "\u00a340,000 - \u00a375,000 + Bonus + Benefits", "comp": "RANGE_45_54K"}}
