{"index": 333, "title": "IT Support Specialist", "job_location": "London, England, United Kingdom", "jd_text": "Job DetailsJob DescriptionMiddlesex University is dedicated to unlocking the full potential of its students and its staff. Our vision is to become a leading university for transforming potential into success.Digital & Library Services are looking for a strong and enthusiastic candidate to join our team as IT Support Specialist, responsible for supporting IT queries and providing technical support to our students and staff. This is an exciting and challenging role for a skilled IT professional, with many opportunities for enhancing existing IT skills and contributing to Universitys Digital & Library Service systems infrastructure.You will be responsible for providing high quality IT Support Services to students and staff in a rich and diverse academic environment. The ability to efficiently manage your time and workload, escalating requests as needed is essential. The role requires you to establish and maintain positive relationships with your customers, seeking to fully understand their requirements and providing solutions and documentation as required.We are looking for a confident and professional individual with excellent interpersonal skills, capable of providing customer care, IT support and guidance to a wide variety of students and staff with a varying level of IT skills. You will be a collaborative team player with the ability to work under your own initiative. Strong technical skills and a willingness to learn, preferably with proven experience of working within an ITIL service management support environment is required.For further information, please contact Sunny Patel, Information Technology Support Manager,Middlesex is committed to fostering an inclusive working environment. We encourage applications from underrepresented groups including people from Black, Asian and minority ethnic groups, disabled people, LGBTQ+ people, women, and gender non-conforming individuals. All recruitment decisions will be based on merit.We value diversity and strive to create a fairer, more equitable work environment for our staff and students. We offer a range of family friendly, inclusive employment policies, flexible working arrangements, staff diversity networks, campus facilities and services to support staff from different backgrounds. Middlesex is home to a diverse community of professionals. We are a bronze award holder of the Athena Swan Charter and the Race Equality Charter, a Stonewall Top 100 employer and Gold award holder in 2023, and a Disability Confident Leader.Job DetailsFaculty/ExecutiveDigital & Library ServicesCompanyMU Services LtdLocationHendonStarting Salary\u00a333,125 to \u00a336,698 per annumGradeGrade 5Contract TypePermanentHours per Week35.5Date PostedTuesday 17 February 2026Closing DateWednesday 04 March 2026Interview DateTo be confirmedReferenceDLS18-RLNKD1_UKTJ\n\nBegin your response with {\n", "v15_labels": {"loc_raw": "London, England, United Kingdom", "loc": "IN_LONDON", "arr_raw": null, "arr": "UNK", "sen_raw": null, "sen": "LEVEL_2", "tech_raw": null, "tech": ["OOS"], "comp_raw": "\u00a333,125 to \u00a336,698 per annum", "comp": "BELOW_45K"}}
{"index": 334, "title": "Software Engineer (all Genders)", "job_location": "Berlin, Germany", "jd_text": "About The CompanyGROPYUS is a technology-based construction company focused on building multi-story residential buildings. Thanks to its prefabricated building system with various design options, industrial offsite construction, and fully digitalized processes, the company manufactures aspirational, sustainable, and affordable homes using timber construction methods. GROPYUS is using scalable construction and manufacturing solutions to tap into a future market, boost Europe's strength in innovation, while also playing a substantial role in improving sustainability.About the Role:You will be part of a highly collaborative product team developing tools that drive and digitize building construction on site at scale.Product Teams at GROPYUS own what they build, including underlying infrastructure, build pipelines, automated testing, release and rollout management, monitoring, and support. You will develop software (both alone and in a pair) that is properly tested and observable, and you will deploy your changes to live systems while ensuring system stability and usabilityYou will be trusted to solve problems efficiently and effectively, and to identify under-attended topics in your product area. You will be expected to work as part of a high-functioning team: working with architectural guidelines, offering support to colleagues, limiting technical debt, spiking solutions to problems, presenting new code and features, and more.What you'll be doing:Designing, building, testing and operating software solutions for building construction use cases incl. inbound logistics, issue tracking, quality assurance, and schedulingWorking alongside our R&D department on an autonomous construction initiativeWorking in a cloud infrastructure environment, managing complex software deploymentsActing as a bridge between digital product delivery & physical construction site activities, 